Hungarian Forint Firms Against Euro, Snapping 3 Days of Losses

-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 
2011-04-14T07:24:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/hungarian-forint-firms-against-euro-snapping-3-days-of-losses.html
The forint strengthened against the
euro for the first time this week.  The Hungarian currency appreciated as much as 0.5 percent,
the biggest intraday advance since April 8, and traded 0.3
percent stronger at 266.32 by 9:08 a.m. in Budapest.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest 
